            <h2 class="card-title">Age Group</h2>
            <p class="card-text">The flu vaccine is recommended annually for almost everyone, with a focus on the following groups:</p>
            <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
              <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Children (6 months and older):</strong> Annual vaccination is strongly recommended.</li>
              <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Adults:</strong> All adults should receive a flu vaccine each year, especially those with chronic health conditions.</li>
              <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Seniors (65+):</strong> High-dose or adjuvanted flu vaccines are recommended for better protection.</li>
              <li class="list-group-item"><strong>Pregnant Women:</strong> Flu vaccine is safe and recommended during pregnancy to protect both mother and baby.</li>
            </ul>
